Intro to REST API architecture

# REST - Representational State Transfer
    Want to craft our endpoints to represent our peices of state

# Resource - Single Item (object) in a database.
/user
typically not used. typically going to be /users/id

# Collection - Collection of similar items in a database.
/users

# Base (root) URL - Such as http://amazon.com

# API endpoint - http://amazon.com/movies
nouns are better than verbs

# Parameters - /movies/:movieId

# Query or query string - /movies?genre=action

# Client - The front end

# Server - Intermediary that receives the requests from the client

# Request Method - CRUD: get, post, put, delete
